WEBVTT

00:12:59.808 --> 00:13:02.301
And my challenge in helping
you grow would be to say,

00:13:02.325 --> 00:13:03.721
"Do you know what those are?

00:13:03.745 --> 00:13:05.332
Do you feel able to channel them

00:13:05.356 --> 00:13:07.642
in a way that helps
and benefits your students?"

00:13:07.666 --> 00:13:13.093
(Music)

00:13:13.117 --> 00:13:16.547
(In the studio) AG: I came away convinced
that Marcus has a valid point.

00:13:16.571 --> 00:13:19.069
The problem isn't always
overusing strengths.

00:13:19.093 --> 00:13:22.464
Sometimes it's misusing them
or using them unintelligently

00:13:22.488 --> 00:13:25.022
or applying them in the wrong situations.

00:13:26.219 --> 00:13:28.512
Melinda Gates: I completely
agree with you, Adam,

00:13:28.536 --> 00:13:32.195
that our greatest weaknesses are sometimes
the other side of our strengths.